nsation claims, payroll, payroll tax compliance, and unemployment insurance claims. They contract with a PEO to assume these responsibilities and provide expertise in human resources management. This allows the PEO client to concentrate on the operational and revenue-producing side of its operations.\n\nA PEO provides integrated services to effectively manage critical human resource responsibilities and employer risks for clients. A PEO delivers these services by establishing and maintaining an employer relationship with the employees at the client’s worksite and by contractually assuming certain employer rights, responsibilities, and risk.\n\nBusinesses across America have discovered the incredible value of PEOs because they provide:\n<ul>\n	<li>Relief from the burden of employment administration.</li>\n	<li>A wide range of personnel management solutions through a team of professionals.</li>\n	<li>Improved employment practices, compliance and risk management to reduce liabilities.</li>\n	<li>Access to a comprehensive employee benefits package, allowing clients to be competitive in the labor market.</li>\n	<li>Assistance to improve productivity and profitability.</li>\n</ul>','What is HR Outsourcing?','','inherit','open','open','','115-autosave','','','2012-06-11 05:09:25','2012-06-11 05:09:25','',115,'http://think.yoshimoshi.com/115-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(129,1,'2012-05-29 23:28:02','2012-05-29 23:28:02','','test2','','inherit','open','open','','113-revision-2','','','2012-05-29 23:28:02','2012-05-29 23:28:02','',113,'http://think.yoshimoshi.com/113-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(130,1,'2012-05-31 05:48:17','2012-05-31 05:48:17','<strong>How can I reduce my employer costs?</strong>\n\nHiring just one employee brings an onslaught of responsibilities. Time spent handling employee-related administration means time you and your people spend away from profitable ventures. Outsourcing these responsibilities to Abel will ensure that every facet is managed professionally, allowing you to focus on your bottom line.\n\n<strong>Is there any way to increase employee productivity?</strong>\n\nWe handle the non-revenue producing duties associated with human resources, payroll, workers’ compensation, risk management and employee benefits so you AND your employees can focus on your business – not the red tape.\n\n<strong>Is there any way to decrease my employer liabilities?</strong>\n\nYou have too much liability in a traditional employment relationship. Federal and state employment regulations have become increasingly complex, forcing you to become an expert in two fields. Why not hire an expert firm, to insure your company against unknown legal requirements, changes in law and frivolous allegations that can result in costly litigation, fines and penalties.\n\n<strong>Why do I have to deal with workers’ compensation?</strong>\n\nWe provide the workers’ compensation for the employees at your company. Since we are dealing with millions of dollars in premiums, we typically arrange better pricing for our clients. We professionally manage our workers’ compensation plans to ensure you pay no more than you have to, along with eliminating the down-payment which can help with cash flow.\n\n<strong>Is there a way to handle risk management and safety issues without it taking up all my time and money?</strong>\n\nWe provide risk management services custom made to fit your worksite’s needs. Through persistent loss control efforts, we can reduce the frequency and severity of claims which, in turn, can reduce claims costs and ultimately your workers’ compensation costs.\n\n<strong>How in the world can I afford to provide better employee benefits?</strong>\n\nThe rising costs of employee benefits are inevitable and most times out of your control. Abel helps its clients to slow these inevitable increases and gain control. In addition your people will gain the availability of a more comprehensive employee benefits plan. By offering more benefits you will be able to attract and retain the best possible people for your organization.\n\n<strong>I outsource my payroll, I lease my car – is there any way to outsource human resources administration so I don’t have to hire another executive?</strong>\n\nHuman resources administration does not generate profit but, non-compliance in employment issues can eat away the profits you do generate. We are a “Professional Employer” and we protect our clients from costly fines and litigation.\n\n<strong>I have a payroll company, an insurance agent for health, another agent for workers’ compensation, an attorney to help with labor law issues, a CPA firm to help with employment tax issues, a company that handles my retirement plan, another to call for benefit questions and I put myself out there occasionally with issues that I am not an expert in – Is there any other way?</strong>\n\nYes there is! The Abel Way! Most companies outsource workers’ compensation insurance, employee benefits, retirement planning, and payroll administration. By using Abel, you can outsource just about all employment-related tasks to one vendor, one expert, one PEO.\n\n<strong>What Abel can do for you?</strong>\n\nThrough Abel you have the ability to access the knowledge of all our professionals in one location. This gives you one-stop shopping for all you need to run and/or administer your employees today. Our company simply allows you to focus on profits and sales.','Why you need Abel','','inherit','open','open','','113-autosave','','','2012-05-31 05:48:17','2012-05-31 05:48:17','',113,'http://think.yoshimoshi.com/113-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(136,1,'2012-05-31 06:01:26','2012-05-31 06:01:26','','Jim3_110','','inherit','open','open','','jim3_110','','','2012-05-31 06:01:26','2012-05-31 06:01:26','',0,'http://think.yoshimoshi.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Jim3_110.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(138,1,'2012-05-31 06:03:57','2012-05-31 06:03:57','<div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n<div class=\"grid_5