ilities, and risk.\r\n\r\nBusinesses across America have discovered the incredible value of PEOs because they provide:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Relief from the burden of employment administration.</li>\r\n	<li>A wide range of personnel management solutions through a team of professionals.</li>\r\n	<li>Improved employment practices, compliance and risk management to reduce liabilities.</li>\r\n	<li>Access to a comprehensive employee benefits package, allowing clients to be competitive in the labor market.</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance to improve productivity and profitability.</li>\r\n</ul>','What is a PEO?','','inherit','open','open','','115-revision-3','','','2012-05-31 05:43:48','2012-05-31 05:43:48','',115,'http://think.yoshimoshi.com/115-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(196,2,'2012-06-07 02:24:03','2012-06-07 02:24:03','','Abel_Avatar','','inherit','open','open','','abel_avatar','','','2012-06-07 02:24:03','2012-06-07 02:24:03','',4,'http://think.yoshimoshi.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Abel_Avatar.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(197,2,'2012-06-07 02:26:22','2012-06-07 02:26:22','','abel_logo','','inherit','open','open','','abel_logo','','','2012-06-07 02:26:22','2012-06-07 02:26:22','',0,'http://think.yoshimoshi.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/abel_logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(198,2,'2012-06-07 02:30:40','2012-06-07 02:30:40','<strong>How can I reduce my employer costs?</strong>\r\n\r\nHiring just one employee brings an onslaught of responsibilities. Time spent handling employee-related administration means time you and your people spend away from profitable ventures. Outsourcing these responsibilities to Abel will ensure that every facet is managed professionally, allowing you to focus on your primary business.\r\n\r\n<strong>Is there any way to increase employee productivity?</strong>\r\n\r\nWe handle the non-revenue producing duties associated with human resources, payroll, workers’ compensation, risk management and employee benefits so you AND your employees can focus on your business – not the red tape.\r\n\r\n<strong>Is there any way to decrease my employer liabilities?</strong>\r\n\r\nIn a traditional employment relationship, you face too much liability exposure. Federal and state employment regulations have become increasingly complex, forcing you to become an expert in two fields. Why not hire an expert firm, to protect your company from unknown legal requirements, changes in the law, and frivolous allegations that can result in costly litigation, fines and penalties.\r\n\r\n<strong>Why do I have to deal with Workers’ Compensation Insurance?</strong>\r\n\r\nAbel would provide the workers’ compensation insurance for the employees at your company. Since we are dealing with millions of dollars in premiums, we typically arrange better pricing for our clients. We professionally manage our workers’ compensation plans to ensure you pay no more than you have to, and eliminate the down-payment which can help with cash flow.\r\n\r\n<strong>Is there a way to handle risk management and safety issues without it taking up all my time and money?</strong>\r\n\r\nWe provide risk management services custom made to fit your worksite’s needs. Through persistent loss control efforts, we can reduce the frequency and severity of claims which, in turn, can reduce claims costs and ultimately your workers’ compensation costs.\r\n\r\n<strong>How in the world can I afford to provide better employee benefits?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe rising costs of employee benefits are inevitable and, for the most part, out of your control. Abel helps its clients slow these increases and gain control. In addition, your people will gain access to a more comprehensive employee benefits plan. By offering more benefits you will be able to attract and retain the best possible people for your organization.\r\n\r\nI have a payroll company, an insurance agent for health, another agent for workers’ compensation, an attorney to help with labor law issues, a CPA firm to help with employment tax issues, a company that handles my retirement plan, another to call for benefit questions and I put myself out there occasionally with issues that I am not an expert in – Is there any other way?\r\n\r\nYes there is! The Abel Way!\r\n\r\nMost companies outsource workers’ compensation insurance, employee benefits, retirement planning, and payroll administration. By using Abel, you can outsource just about all employment-related tasks to one vendor, one expert, one PEO.\r\n\r\n<strong>What Abel can do for me?</strong>\r\n\r\nThrough Abel you have the ability to access the knowledge of all our professionals in one location. This gives you one-stop shopping for all you need to run and/or administer your employees today. Abel simply allows you to focus on profits and sales.','Why You Need Abel','','publish','open','open','','why-you-need-abel','','','2012-06-20 06:18:22','2012-06-20 06:18:22','',95,'http://think.yoshimoshi.com/?page_id=198',2,'page','',0),(199,2,'2012-06-07 02:30:12','2012-06-07 02:30:12','','Why You Need Abel','','inherit','open','open','','198-revision','','','2012-06-07 02:30:12','2012-06-07 02:30:12','',198,'http://think.yoshimoshi.com/198-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(332,2,'2012-05-31 05:31:11','2012-05-31 05:31:11','<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#01\">What is a Professional Employer Organization?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#02\">What type of companies use PEOs?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#03\">Why use a PEO?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#04\">Why choose Abel?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#05\">What makes Abel different from other PEOs?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#06\">Why is Abel PEO Services better than a payroll service?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#07\">How can I determine whether a PEO is a reputable and financially stable company?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#08\">How long has Abel been in business?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#09\">Will I be giving up control of my employees?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#10\">How do employees of the business usually accept Abel?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#11\">What does Abel provide for their clients?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#12\">What makes the benefits package better with Abel?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#13\">How can Abel negotiate better rates than I can get on benefits?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#14\">What type of healthcare benefits does Abel offer?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.thinkabel.com/wp/faq#15\">What workers’ compensation functions does Abel perform?\r\n\r\n</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<strong>What is a Professional Employer Organization?</strong>\r\n\r\nProfessional employer organizations (PEOs) enable clients to cost-effectively outsource the management of human resources, employee benefits, payroll and workers’ compensation. PEO clients focus on their core competencies to maintain and grow their bottom line.\r\n\r\nBusinesses today need help managing increasingly complex employee related matters such as health benefits, workers’ compensation claims, payroll, payroll tax compliance, and unemployment insurance claims. They contract with a PEO to assume these responsibilities and provide expertise in human resources management. This allows the PEO client to concentrate on the operational and revenue-producing side of its operations.\r\n\r\nA PEO provides integrated services for clients to effectively manage critical human resource responsibilities and employer risks. A PEO delivers these services by establishing and maintaining an employer relationship with the employees at the client’s work site and by contractually assuming certain employer rights, responsibilities, and risks.\r\n\r\nBusinesses across America have discovered the incredible value of PEOs because they provide:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Relief from the burden of employment administration.</li>\r\n	<li>A wide range of personnel management solutions through a team of professionals.</li>\r\n	<li>Improved employment practices, compliance and risk management to reduce liabilities.</li>\r\n	<li>Access to a comprehensive employee benefits package, allowing clients to be competitive in the labor market.</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance to improve productivity and profitability.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>__________</strong>_____\r\n\r\n<strong>What type of companies use PEOs?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe companies that utilize PEO services all have one thing in common. They are looking to increase their competitiveness. With increased benefits and human resource expertise, PEOs give employers the opportunity to attract better employees and retain existing employees. Additionally, with increased human resource expertise, PEOs assist employers in labor law compliance and handle all the filing and paperwork associated with such efforts. As a result, employers are able to devote more time to their core competencies. PEO clients represent all industries, serving many types of companies across the nation.\r\n\r\n<strong>__________</strong>_____\r\n\r\n<strong>Why use a PEO?</strong>\r\n\r\nMost business owners will agree, they did not start a business to handle the many complexities that accompany the hiring of just their first employee. Nevertheless, today’s business owners are spending an ever-increasing amount of time and effort managing employee-related matters.\r\n\r\nOur concept is simple – instead of spending your valuable time on unproductive, exhausting paperwork and administration – delegate these tasks to Abel, a professional firm with expertise in every facet of the employer-employee relationship. This allows owners and managers to return their focus to the revenue-producing aspects of their business.\r\n\r\n<strong>__________</strong>_____\r\n\r\n<strong>Why choose Abel?</strong>\r\n\r\nAbel has the necessary expertise in the management of human resources administration, payroll and payroll taxes, workers’ compensation insurance, and employee benefits because it’s our only business. Our clients eliminate the risk of costly errors, fines, and penalties because Abel assumes the responsibility for the compliance issues that can cause them. We are “Abel” to generate cost savings for our clients by using our management experience, excellent ratings, and good standing to reduce certain specific employer costs.\r\n\r\n<strong>__________</strong>_____\r\n\r\n<strong>What makes Abel different from other PEOs?</strong>\r\n\r\nAt Abel, our mission is to provide the very best of what a PEO relationship can offer at the best possible price to an ever expanding base of clients and leased employees. We will supply these services to our clients and our leased employees with the highest regard for the personal service that is expected from a family-owned and operated business.\r\n\r\nWe believe that in order to do justice to the employer relationship, all employer responsibilities must be assumed completely by Abel without the need for the Client to “read the fine print” of our service agreement. When exceptional issues occur, they will be handled with the clients’ and the employees’ best interests in mind.\r\n\r\nWe are not a company focused on selling insurance or financial services such as payroll and/or retirement planning. We are a firm that provides Comprehensive Human Resources Management that includes many of the benefits larger, more progressive companies use to their advantage.\r\n\r\n<strong>__________</strong>_____\r\n\r\n<strong>Why is Abel PEO Services better than a payroll service?</strong>\r\n\r\nAbel’s services are much more comprehensive than a payroll service provider. Abel not only administers your payroll but has numerous specialists managing your workers’ compensation, unemployment and benefit programs, as well as handling regulatory compliance, filing and record keeping, and human resources.\r\n\r\n<strong>__________</strong>_____\r\n\r\n<strong>How can I determine whether a PEO is a reputable and financially stable company?</strong>\r\n\r\nNo matter what PEO you consider, you should investigate its background diligently.\r\n\r\n<strong>First</strong>, check to see if the PEO is licensed or registered with the state. Certain states, like New Jersey, require PEOs to be licensed and satisfy strict reporting requirements.\r\n\r\n<strong>Second</strong>, check to see if the company is an active member of the National Association of Professional Employer Organizations (NAPEO) – an organization that works with regulatory and legislative bodies to monitor the PEO industry, as well as the New Jersey Association of PEOs.\r\n\r\n<strong>Third</strong>, ask for client and professional references.\r\n\r\n<strong>Fourth and foremost</strong>, ask for financial audit information to make certain that the PEO has paid payroll taxes and insurance premiums in a timely fashion for its clients over a substantial period of time.\r\n\r\n<strong>__________</strong>_____\r\n\r\n<strong>How long has Abel been in business?</strong>\r\n\r\nAbel was founded by its President, James W. Bell Sr. in 1992. We offer the highest level of service available in the market today to hundreds of businesses and thousands of employees in varying industries across the nation.\r\n\r\n<strong>__________</strong>_____\r\n\r\n<strong>Will I be giving up control of my employees?</strong>\r\n\r\nNo. In a PEO relationship you do not relinquish control of your employees. What you are giving up are the countless back-office administrative and human resource tasks and headaches involved in having employees on your payroll. Abel is an off-site human resources consultant group that serves as your administrative employer only. You remain the on-site employer, in charge of everyday operational decisions that affect your company’s bottom line.\r\n\r\n<strong>__________</strong>_____\r\n\r\n<strong>How do employees of the business usually accept Abel?</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce employees understand that they will be receiving better employee benefits, they readily accept the new relationship. For our clients, increased employee benefits have resulted in higher morale and decreased turnover — another benefit to businesses contracting with a professional employer organization.\r\n\r\n<strong>__________</strong>_____\r\n\r\n<strong>What does Abel provide for their clients?</strong>\r\n\r\nExtensive Management Experience in All Aspects of the Employer-Employee Relationship:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Solid Reputation and Industry Leadership</li>\r\n	<li>Family-Owned and Operated</li>\r\n	<li>Full-Time On-Site Safety and Risk Management</li>\r\n	<li>Monthly CPA Confirmation of Payroll Tax Payments</li>\r\n	<li>Multiple Health Benefit Options</li>\r\n	<li>Qualified 401(k) Plan</li>\r\n	<li>HR Support Includes Recruiting</li>\r\n	<li>Direct Deposit and Direct Debit at No Charge</li>\r\n	<li>Popular Credit Union Memberships</li>\r\n	<li>Outstanding Employee Assistance Program</li>\r\n	<li>On-Site and/or Local Management Training</li>\r\n	<li>Extensive employee perks that include discounts on Movie/Theater Tickets, Insurance, Theme Parks, Pet Insurance and More!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>__________</strong>_____\r\n\r\n<strong>What makes the benefits package better with Abel?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe employees of Abel are part of a large corporation that is constantly growing. Our size and our growth enable us to provide our employees with an ever-increasing host of benefits. Abel’s employee benefits package is so comprehensive that it allows our clients to compete with major corporations in attracting and retaining the highest quality employees.\r\n\r\n<strong>__________</strong>_____\r\n\r\n<strong>How can Abel negotiate better rates than I can get on benefits?</strong>\r\n\r\nAs an employer of thousands, we enjoy greater economies of scale when purchasing employee benefits. This not only applies to employee medical benefits (i.e. health and dental insurances) and financial benefits — i.e. 401(k) and Section 125 –but also to workers’ compensation rates. We often can negotiate better workers’ compensation rates because our claims experience is spread over a much larger number of employees.\r\n\r\n<strong>__________</strong>_____\r\n\r\n<strong>What type of healthcare benefits does Abel offer?</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Medical Insurance –</strong> Abel offers various medical insurance plans to full-time, eligible employees.\r\n\r\n<strong>Dental –</strong> Realizing that all dentists and all dental care needs cannot be covered under one plan design, Abel offers several optional programs for dental care.\r\n\r\n<strong>Vision –</strong> At a time when vision care is being watered down to a small benefit offered in conjunction with medical plans, a separate vision care plan is becoming a necessity.\r\n\r\n<strong>Prescription Drug – </strong>Abel’s prescription drug benefit provider’s participating pharmacy network is nationwide in scope and includes both independent pharmacies and chain stores. Over 95% of all pharmacies will accept our current prescription card.\r\n\r\n<strong>Life –</strong> Our Basic Life policy provides Group Term Life with Accidental Death and Dismemberment coverage and is mandatory for all participants in any Abel medical plan or can be elected as a stand-alone policy.\r\n\r\n<strong>__________</strong>_____\r\n\r\n<strong>What workers’ compensation functions does Abel perform?</strong>\r\n\r\nYour employees are covered by Abel’s policy with each client receiving its own individual policy as required by state and federal law, so you have no prepayment of premium, finance charge, deposit, audit and punitive rate responsibilities. We provide loss control, risk management, claims management, year-end audits, employee safety programs, processing of forms, follow-up on claims and litigation, and filing of all notices and certificates of insurance. We will provide updates on new legal requirements in the care of injured workers, as well as provide a managed care program.','FAQ','','inherit','open','open','','97-revision-3','','','2012-05-31 05:31:11','2012-05-31 05:31:11','',97,'http://think.yoshimoshi.com/97-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(200,2,'2012-06-07 02:31:16','2012-06-07 02:31:16','<h2>CPA’s</h2>\r\n<em>Why should you refer your customers to Abel?</em>\r\n\r\n1. Abel is audited on a monthly basis by an independent CPA firm. You can refer Abel to your clients without having to worry about your reputation.\r\n\r\n2. We have a solid reputation for Industry Leadership for more than 20 years.\r\n\r\n3. Abel will simply allow your clients to focus on running their company instead of all of the non-productive details that we deal with day in and day out.\r\n<h2>Brokers</h2>\r\nBrokers are stating the following more and more often: “I just lost this or that case to a PEO.”\r\n\r\n<em>Abel’s PEO solution will wrap up in one package the ability to manage:</em>\r\n\r\n1. Payroll Administration\r\n\r\n2. Human Resource Administration\r\n\r\n3. Benefits Administration\r\n\r\n4. Billing Administration\r\n\r\n5. COBRA Administration\r\n\r\n6. FSA Administration\r\n\r\n7. Pension Administration\r\n\r\n8. Workers’ Compensation and Safety\r\n\r\n9. The proverbial One-Stop Shopping\r\n\r\n<strong>We are ‘broker friendly’ and are looking for broker-partners to promote our service. We will enable you to provide more services to your existing customers.</strong>','Trusted Advisors','','publish','open','open','','trusted-advisors','','','2012-06-20 06:18:43','2012-06-20 06:18:43','',95,'http://think.yoshimoshi.com/?page_id=200',3,'page','',0),(201,2,'2012-06-07 02:30:59','2012-06-07 02:30:59','','Trus